name: #2 ISLA DIABLO, GUNA YALA ARCHIPELAGO, PANAMA 2014
description:
Despite its name, Isla Diablo is the pretty girl of the northern Gulf of San Blas. It is a group of clear water islands located in the Limones Cays, and is known for the sandbanks and coral reefs that protect them from the Caribbean Sea: the ideal destination if you like to explore the aquatic life.

Isla Diablo belongs to the San Blas Archipelago, Panama. It is inhabited by the Guna Yala ethnic group.

Guna Yala, formerly known as San Blas, is a comarca indígena (indigenous province) in northeast Panama. Guna Yala is home to the indigenous people known as the Gunas. Its capital is Gaigirgordub. It is bounded on the north by the Caribbean Sea, on the south by the Darién Province and Emberá-Wounaan, on the east by Colombia, and on the west by the province of Colón.
